column1: #Text=Chickasaw National Recreation Area is in Chickasaw Country of United States .
#Text=The Chickasaw National Recreation Area is easily accessible from Highway 7 and Highway 77 in Sulphur ( Oklahoma ) .
#Text=The National Park Service offices is located in the Chickasaw Visitor Center , adjacent to The Artesian Hotel at Highway 7 and Highway 77 .
#Text=There are no fees to enter the park .
#Text=The Chickasaw National Recreation Area is free for drive-up and walk-up visitors .
#Text=Non-utility campsite : $ 14.00 - Cold Springs , Guy Sandy , & Rock Creek Campgrounds .
#Text=Utility campsite : $ 22.00 - Buckhorn and the Point Campgrounds , and one site at Rock Creek Campground
#Text=Premium utility site : $ 24.00 ( May through September ) - Buckhorn Campground , Loop D sites #24 , 25 , 26 and Buckhorn Campground , Loop C sites #4 , 5 , 6 , 7
#Text=Group sites : $ 30.00 - Rock Creek , Cold Springs & Central Campgrounds
#Text=Persons may camp up to 14 consecutive days , not to exceed 30 days total between Memorial Day and Labor Day .
#Text=The Senior or Access Pass 50 % discount applies only to individual campsites and lake launching permits , not group sites .
#Text=There are covered picnic pavilions located in the Buckhorn and Veteran 's Lake areas .
#Text=They are available by reservation for $ 30 per day .
#Text=You can hike , swim , hunt , or go boating in the recreation area .
#Text=Open year-round , the Travertine Nature Center has opportunities for learning , classes and nature exhibits .
#Text=Live , interactive learning is available for all ages .
#Text=Open year-round except Christmas , Thanksgiving , New Year 's Day .
#Text=There are several campgrounds within the Chickasaw National Recreation Area :
#Text=Central Campground ( available just off Highway 77 after entering the park ) , ☏ +1-877-444-6777 .
#Text=Seasonal public campground in the Chickasaw National Recreation Area 's Platt Historic District .
#Text=Cold Springs Campground ( across the road from Travertine Creek ) , ☏ +1-877-444-6777 .
#Text=Sites are non-electrical and best suited for tent camping , but small RVs and pop-up campers may fit .
#Text=Amenities : Water spigots and restrooms located close to camp sites .
#Text=Rock Creek Campground ( near Veterans Lake and Rock Creek ) .
#Text=Year-round campground near Veterans Lake and Rock Creek .
#Text=There is easy access to hiking trails , fishing and mineral springs .
#Text=105 campsites and 1 group site are available for tent camping .
#Text=Amenities include water spigots and restrooms close to campsites .
#Text=All sites are first come , first served with showers available in restrooms .
#Text=Some sites have electrical and water hookups available .
#Text=utility : $ 22 per night , premium utility : $ 24 per night , non-utility : $ 16 per night .
#Text=In the Arbuckle District of the park , Guy Sandy has 40 campsites available on a first come , first served basis .
#Text=Turner Falls Park : A beautiful natural waterfall in the Arbuckle Mountains .
